export const BUTTON_BUILD_SPEC = "# KENT WEB DESIGN — BUTTON BUILD SPEC (concrete, mechanics not vibes)\n> For the automated portal build. The master prompt is the philosophy; THIS is the executable spec.\n> Rule of thumb: if a line here is a vibe (\"premium\", \"bold\"), it's wrong — replace with a number or a named choice.\n\n## 0. Priority (when torn, obey this)\n1) Looks premium + works. 2) Converts (calls). 3) SEO. Never template-generic.\n\n## 1. COMMIT TO ONE STYLE (do this first, state it in design_rationale)\nPick the ONE style below that best fits the client's **logo colours + trade + brief**, then execute its numbers exactly. Do not blend styles. Do not default to the same one each time.\n\n| Style | Fits | Base | Accent use | Radius | Shadow | Motion feel |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Minimal-Premium** | clean/pro trades, B2B, clinics | white + one neutral | one accent, sparing | 12–16px | soft, low | calm 200–250ms |\n| **Warm-Trust** | domestic trades (heating, roofing, electrical) | warm off-white / deep navy | strong single accent | 14–20px | medium soft | confident reveals |\n| **Dark-Cinematic** | premium, solar, security, automotive | near-black + charcoal | 1 glowing accent | 16–22px | deep, layered | dramatic, slow parallax |\n| **Editorial-Bold** | agencies, design-led, gyms | off-white + ink | high-contrast accent | 4–10px | crisp | snappy, big type moves |\n| **Glass-Modern** | tech, SaaS-ish, energy | tinted gradient bg | vivid accent | 18–24px | blurred glass | smooth floats |\n\n## 2. PALETTE — sample from the logo, define exact tokens\n```\n--brand:      <primary logo colour>\n--brand-700:  <darker shade, ~20% darker> (hovers, depth)\n--accent:     <one popping colour from logo/complement> (ALL CTAs, only this)\n--ink:        #14181f   --muted: #5a6472   --line: #e6e9ef\n--bg:         <style base>   --surface: <section alt bg>   --dark: <dark-section bg>\n--grad:       linear-gradient(...) from brand→brand-700 (hero veil, dark bands)\n```\nOne accent, everywhere CTAs. Never introduce a random colour not derived here.\n\n## 3. TYPE — concrete scale (pick a pairing that fits the style; from DESIGN-INTELLIGENCE table)\n```\n--display: <heading font>   --body: <body font>   (Google Fonts, preconnect + swap)\nHero H1:  font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 7vw, 6rem); weight: 800–900; line-height: 1.02; letter-spacing: -0.02em\nH2:       clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem); weight: 700; line-height: 1.1\nH3:       clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.6rem); weight: 600\nBody:     1rem (min 16px); line-height: 1.6; max 70ch per line\nEyebrow:  0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; uppercase; --muted\n```\nTimid type is the #1 generic tell. Hero headline must be BIG and confident.\n\n## 4. SPACING — 8pt scale, never edge-to-edge\n```\nSection padding-block: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem)\nContainer: max-width: 1200px; margin-inline: auto; padding-inline: clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 2rem)   ← never 0\nGap scale: 8 / 16 / 24 / 40 / 64 px. Card padding ≥ 24px. Nothing touches the screen edge on any breakpoint.\n```\n\n## 5. HERO — concrete recipe (the make-or-break section)\n- **min-height: 88vh** (use `svh` for iOS), content vertically centred, an **asymmetric** layout (not dead-centre stacked).\n- Order: eyebrow pill (badge) → **oversized H1** with **one `<span class=\"accent\">` word** → subhead (≤ 2 lines) → **2 buttons** (primary = solid `--accent`; secondary = outline) → stat row **only if the stats are real from the brief** (else omit — never invent).\n- **Background:** real photo if available → else a designed CSS scene (gradient mesh + shapes + big type) → else a clean AI scene. ALWAYS a `--grad` veil ≥ 70% over any photo/AI so text is crisp and no image-content is legible.\n- Depth: separate foreground text from background (overlay, blur, or a floating glass card with a key proof point).\n\n## 6. IMAGES — hard rules (this is what broke on Sunvera)\n- **Logo:** always the client's REAL asset. NEVER AI-generated. Never let AI render text/letters/signage.\n- **AI images:** last resort only; **clean text-free scenes**; **always ≥70% overlay** when behind text; never raw full-bleed.\n- **Brand-personal touch:** generate a clean scene, then **composite the real logo on top** (CSS/SVG) — branded van, badge, signage. Personal + believable.\n- Every `<img>`: `width`/`height` set (zero CLS), `loading=\"lazy\"` below fold, `object-fit: cover`, descriptive alt.\n\n## 7. SECTIONS — assemble from the proven library (brief decides which)\nSticky centred-nav header · hero (above) · trust strip (3–4 real reassurances) · service cards (1 per real service, real substance) · numbered how-it-works · guarantees/why-us (real promises) · reviews grid (REAL only) · FAQ accordion (+FAQPage schema) · areas-we-cover (real towns) · CTA bands between sections · photo footer w/ knockout logo + NAP + \"Built by Kent Web Design\". No duplicated sections.\n\n## 8. MOTION — Lenis + GSAP via CDN (fundamentals stay correct regardless)\nLenis smooth-scroll; GSAP ScrollTrigger for staggered section reveals (y:24, stagger 0.06, 0.5s), hero entrance, parallax on media, animated stat counters. `transform`/`opacity` only. `prefers-reduced-motion` disables. Lazy-init; stay Lighthouse-90. Motion is ON TOP of correct spacing/type/overlay — never instead of them. No preloaders.\n\n## 9. CONVERSION\nSticky mobile tap-to-call bar (phones). `tel:` on every number. CTA band every ~2 sections. Form: visible labels, inline validation, honeypot, on-page success (no reload), job-type → email subject.\n\n## 10. SEO (after looks) — quiet but complete\nOne keyword-led H1/page, unique title+meta+canonical+OG, LocalBusiness/FAQPage JSON-LD, semantic headings, real NAP identical sitewide. Don't let this section bloat the visual work.\n\n## ❌ NEVER (instant-generic tells)\nGarbled AI text · AI logo · emoji as icons · edge-to-edge text · dead-centre stacked boxes on every section · timid small headings · a colour not from the palette · fabricated stats/reviews/accreditations · the same layout as the last build.\n";
